The paper investigates social learning in the context of human cognitive abilities, specifically analytical reasoning. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of social networks (cs.SOC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), machine learning (cs.LG), and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Additionally, the laboratory-based experiments conducted in the paper involve network experiments, which could also place it in the sub-category of social networks (cs.SOC). However, since the paper focuses on the limitations of social learning, it is most likely to belong to the sub-category of social influence (cs.SI).
